dct_title_s: ORBIS TERRARUM COGNITUS VETERIBUS GRAECIS ET LATINIS
dct_description_sm: Dedicated to Jacobo Dno. Compton, Honmi. Comitis Northamptoniae, with coat of arms between the two hemispheres.
Issued with similar world map (Entry #1011), which shows the modern world with all of the continents named.

Issued in: Geographia Emendata & Locupletata, / Dionysius Periegetes, 1688. Reissued in 1704, 1718 (Editio tertia), 1726 (Editio quarta, with Typis Guil. Bowyer), and 1738 (Editio quinta, with Typis T. Wood).
California with a single indentation along the northern coast and blank to its north. The continents in the western hemisphere are unnamed as they were unknown to the ancients.
